sql:
SELECT anchor_text
FROM backlinks
WHERE link_quality > (SELECT AVG(link_quality) FROM backlinks);

SELECT COUNT(*) AS total_high_quality_links
FROM backlinks
WHERE link_quality > 70 AND client_id = 1;

SELECT backlink_id 
FROM backlinks 
WHERE client_id = 1;

SELECT MAX(domain_authority) AS max_domain_authority
FROM refdomains
WHERE page_rank = (SELECT MAX(page_rank) FROM refdomains);

SELECT refdomain_name, domain_authority
FROM refdomains
WHERE ip_address = '192.168.1.1';

SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT backlink_id) AS unique_backlinks_count
FROM backlinks
WHERE client_id = 1;

external_knowledge:
- 'grand total of distinct connections' refers to the total number of unique backlinks;
- 'players on the field' refers to clients who own active backlinks;
- External knowledge: In this context, a backlink is considered 'active' if its status is 'active', indicating it is functioning as intended and directing users to the correct location.
